  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Cachexia and low nutritional intake are a common phenomena in cancer patients undergoing
      chemotherapy. The purpose of this study is to assess prevalence of cachexia and low
      nutritional intake and the impact on quality of life, fatigue and mortality in patients
      undergoing chemotherapy. Furthermore interactions between these parameters, tumor disease and
      chemotherapy, respectively.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
